We need to reset in finally so that even if exception occurs, the static fields are cleared. Also, we should ensure that the reset happens before returning.

Fix:

```
public static Option create(String opt) throws IllegalArgumentException
{
    Option option = null;
    try {
        // create the option
        option = new Option(opt, description);

        // set the option properties
        option.setLongOpt(longopt);
        option.setRequired(required);
        option.setOptionalArg(optionalArg);
        option.setArgs(numberOfArgs);
        option.setType(type);
        option.setValueSeparator(valuesep);
        option.setArgName(argName);
    } finally {
        // reset the OptionBuilder properties
        OptionBuilder.reset();
    }

    // return the Option instance
    return option;
}
```

But note: if exception occurs in new Option(), the option is null, but we still reset. That's fine. If exception occurs in setter, we still reset. The return will be after the finally block, but if exception occurred, it will propagate after finally. This ensures reset is always called.

Also, we must consider that the static fields are used in the Option constructor. So the reset must happen after the constructor. The above fix does that.

